    <div class="page__inner-wrap">
      
        <header>
          <h1 class="page__title" itemprop="headline">Propulsion System - Patented Design
</h1>
          
        
        
        
        
             
        
    
        </header>
      

      <section class="page__content" itemprop="text">
        <p>LIM, short for Linear Induction Motor, is the pod’s primary propulsion system and provides the thrust required for the pod’s acceleration. We have achieved a compact design with just a 12kg, 70cm long LIM. We introduced a new design, using curved tooth to curb the end effects.  All our simulations were done using COMSOL Multiphysics software and tested.
We patented our new design on 27th April, 2022.</p>

<h2 id="patent">Patent</h2>

<p><strong>Enhanced Linear Induction Motor (LIM) with a modified end-teeth design</strong>
Nikhil Yelamarthy, Parth Shah, <strong><em>Shivaprasad Hulyal</em></strong>, Kishan Thakkar, Dr. Satyanaryanan Chakravarthy
<em>(Patent Application No: 202241024672)</em></p>

<p>In July 2021, we won the ‘Most Scalable Pod Design’ by Zeleros Hyperloop at the European Hyperloop Week at Valencia, Spain.</p>

<p>We were presented on all major news houses as well as local coverage in India due to our work on the Hyperloop. All the news coverage can be found <a href="https://shivaprasaduh.github.io//files/Avishkar/avishkar_news.pdf">here.</a></p>

<p>For more information visit the team’s official website <a href="https://www.avishkarhyperloop.com">www.avishkarhyperloop.com</a></p>

